President Barack Obama has nominated Judge Pamela Pepper to serve on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Wisconsin. Judge Pepper has been the Chief Bankruptcy Judge in the Eastern District of Wisconsin since 2010 and has a long and distinguished record of service. She has also worked as a criminal defense attorney, handled trials and appeals in state and federal courts, and served as an Assistant United States Attorney in both the Eastern District of Wisconsin and the Northern District of Illinois. Judge Pepper received her J.D. from Cornell Law School and her B.S. from Northwestern University.